274\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Mai 13, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yno1665703531917.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yno1665703531917.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yno1665703531917.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yno1665703531917\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                       \n Settings: Triggers\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Choose the triggers you want to be enabled or disabled for debugging, or those that you want to be set as breakpoints.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yno1665703531917__p_d175823e1_d175824e1_d175825e1\">All triggers are enabled by default except the preDisplay trigger. When a trigger is disabled, the Debugger cannot be used to step through its ProcScript statements.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yno1665703531917__section_dpd_1qh_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d559714e58\">Fields</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yno1665703531917__p_d175829e1_d175830e1_d175831e1\">The tab displays a list of the Uniface trigger names\n        (abbreviated), starting with application-level triggers, followed by component-level, and so\n        on, down to menu-item level. Within each group of triggers, the abbreviations are sorted\n        alphabetically.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yno1665703531917__p_d175832e1_d175833e1_d175834e1\">For each trigger you can specify one of the following\n          <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Setting</span> values:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yno1665703531917__table_d18512e1_d18513e1_d18514e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yno1665703531917__table_d18512e1_d18513e1_d18514e1__entry__1\">Setting </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yno1665703531917__table_d18512e1_d18513e1_d18514e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yno1665703531917__table_d18512e1_d18513e1_d18514e1__entry__1\">Enabled </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yno1665703531917__table_d18512e1_d18513e1_d18514e1__entry__2\">Trigger is enabled for debugging. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yno1665703531917__table_d18512e1_d18513e1_d18514e1__entry__1\">Disabled </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yno1665703531917__table_d18512e1_d18513e1_d18514e1__entry__2\">Trigger cannot be debugged. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yno1665703531917__table_d18512e1_d18513e1_d18514e1__entry__1\">Break </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yno1665703531917__table_d18512e1_d18513e1_d18514e1__entry__2\">Trigger is set as a breakpoint. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ayx1665702860536.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Breakpoints</a><p>A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ibc1665703531301.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: I/O Print</a><p>Choose the level of I/O messages that are displayed in the message frame or transcript window.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ppp1665703531653.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Tracing</a><p>Choose the level or type of ProcScript-related tracing to be displayed in the message frame or transcript window.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uha1665703532184.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Errors</a><p>Set a specific ProcScript error value ($procerror) as a breakpoint.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sev1665703532366.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Message Frame</a><p>Specify whether the clrmess ProcScript instruction is enabled or disabled, and whether application messages are sent to the application's message frame or to the application's transcript window.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8424274\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8424274\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Settings: Triggers Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Mai 13, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Settings: Triggers Choose the triggers you want to be enabled or disabled for debugging, or those that you want to be set as breakpoints. All triggers are enabled by default except the preDisplay trigger. When a trigger is disabled, the Debugger cannot be used to step through its ProcScript statements. Fields The tab displays a list of the Uniface trigger names (abbreviated), starting with application-level triggers, followed by component-level, and so on, down to menu-item level. Within each group of triggers, the abbreviations are sorted alphabetically. For each trigger you can specify one of the following Setting values: Setting Description Enabled Trigger is enabled for debugging. Disabled Trigger cannot be debugged. Break Trigger is set as a breakpoint. Related Links Breakpoints A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution. Settings: I/O Print Choose the level of I/O messages that are displayed in the message frame or transcript window. Settings: Tracing Choose the level or type of ProcScript-related tracing to be displayed in the message frame or transcript window. Settings: Errors Set a specific ProcScript error value ($procerror) as a breakpoint. Settings: Message Frame Specify whether the clrmess ProcScript instruction is enabled or disabled, and whether application messages are sent to the application's message frame or to the application's transcript window. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}